  "prompt": "Should I buy Intex Aqua 5.5 VR or Moto E3 Power considering both are under my budget and I like to change my phone every year?",
  "response": "When deciding between the **Intex Aqua 5.5 VR** and the **Moto E3 Power**, it's important to consider your usage preferences and priorities, especially since you plan to change your phone every year. Here's a comparison to help you decide:\n\n---\n\n### **Intex Aqua 5.5 VR**\n- **Pros**:\n  - VR-ready display (5.5-inch HD).\n  - Comes with VR headset included.\n  - Affordable price.\n  - Decent battery life (2800mAh).\n- **Cons**:\n  - Mediocre build quality.\n  - Average camera performance.\n  - Limited software updates and support.\n  - Slower chipset (MediaTek MTK6737) for gaming or multitasking.\n\n---\n\n### **Moto E3 Power**\n- **Pros**:\n  - Better build quality and design.\n  - Near-stock Android experience (cleaner UI, faster updates).\n  - Reliable performance for basic tasks (MediaTek MT6735P).\n  - Good battery life (3500mAh).\n  - Better brand reputation and resale value.\n- **Cons**:\n  - Smaller display (5-inch HD).\n  - No VR support.\n\n---\n\n### **Recommendation**\nIf you prioritize **VR experiences** and want a slightly larger display, the **Intex Aqua 5.5 VR** could be a fun choice for casual use. However, if you value **better build quality, smoother performance, and software reliability**, the **Moto E3 Power** is the better option for day-to-day use.\n\nSince you change your phone every year, the **Intex Aqua 5.5 VR** might offer a novelty factor, but the **Moto E3 Power** is a more dependable and well-rounded device. \n\nUltimately, choose based on your priorities: **fun and VR** (Intex) or **reliability and usability** (Moto).",
